HEADWORD: gonadotropin
<hw>gonadotropin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiology)</fld> <def>A
hormone secreted by the pituitary gland and placenta, which stimulates
the gonads and controls reproductive activity.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gonadotropic hormone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

